body:
To learn more, see [Compass](atlas-connect-via-compass).

On the Database screen, expand the name of the
database, `sample_airbnb`, then click the name of the collection,
`listingsAndReviews`.

- Click the Indexes tab, then select Search Indexes.

- Click Create Atlas Search Index to open the index creation dialog box.

- Enter `vector_index` as the name of the index.

- Define the MongoDB Vector Search index.

  ```json
  {
    "fields": [
      {
        "type": "autoEmbed",
        "modality": "text",
        "path": "summary",
        "model": "voyage-4"
      },
      {
        "type": "filter",
        "path": "address.country"
      },
      {
        "type": "filter",
        "path": "bedrooms"
      }
    ]
  }
  ```

- Click Create Search Index.
